This plugin allows you to style and configure a container that replaces a current
select. It retains most of the default select features.

USE:
At the moment there are no parameters needed or used in initiating the plugin.
You simply pass in your select and call the .sexySelectBox() function.

example:	$('select').sexySelectBox();

FEATURES:
	- Automatically sets tabindex
	- Automatically grabs the value of the corresponding select and displays the text
	- Navigate through the dropdown using arrow keys
	- Fully customiziable via CSS
	- Automatically sets the value of the hidden select


The select box markup looks like the following:

	<div class="sexySelect" id="sexySelect-0" count="0">
	
		<div class="sexySelectCover" count="0" tabindex="0">
			<span>Value of Select</span>
		</div><!--end of sexySelectCover"-->
	
		<dl class="sexySelectMenu" count="0">
			<dt class="sexySelectOptGroup">This is an optgroup title</dt>
			<dd class="sexySelectOpt">This is an option</dd>
		</dl><!--end of sexySelectMenu"-->

	</div><!--end of sexySelect-->
